26:34.220 --> 26:37.520
Yeah, it's really kinda--
kinda hard

26:37.520 --> 26:40.350
when you set there and write
your own funeral song.

26:41.600 --> 26:44.020
♪ Tonight I feel ♪

26:46.020 --> 26:49.060
♪ Like an old violin ♪

26:49.060 --> 26:51.730
Man:
Yeah, yeah.
All right.

26:51.730 --> 26:54.520
♪ Soon to be put away ♪

26:55.850 --> 26:59.520
♪ Never played again ♪

26:59.520 --> 27:02.140
It makes me cry also,
just like they are,

27:02.140 --> 27:05.060
because you can't help
but love the guy.

27:05.060 --> 27:06.270
He was such a genius.

27:06.270 --> 27:08.060
Johnny:
♪ I can't say ♪

27:08.060 --> 27:11.390
Swamp: I talked to him
a few times on the telephone
before he passed,

27:11.390 --> 27:13.390
and I said, "Man,
I got some great songs.

27:13.390 --> 27:17.390
I'd like to come to Nashville
and... and do 'em."

27:17.390 --> 27:20.220
♪ Well, I guess
it's 'cause the truth ♪

27:21.310 --> 27:24.390
♪ Is the hardest thing
I ever faced ♪

27:24.390 --> 27:29.680
Gary: You know,
Johnny Paycheck was a pretty
rough scoundrel and outlaw.

27:29.680 --> 27:32.220
He had good points
and he had bad points,

27:32.220 --> 27:36.060
but in the end,
his good points
outweighed the bad.

27:36.060 --> 27:38.180
♪ And just like that,
it hit me ♪

27:41.180 --> 27:44.180
♪ Well, that old violin
and I were just alike ♪

27:47.350 --> 27:50.390
♪ We'd give our all
to music, and soon ♪

27:51.980 --> 27:54.060
♪ We'll give our life ♪

27:54.060 --> 27:56.390
♪ ♪

27:56.390 --> 27:58.930
Gary:
The last thing
he said to me was,

27:58.930 --> 28:00.810
"Hey, Gary,
I owe you one."

28:00.810 --> 28:02.980
I said,
"You don't owe me nothing."

28:07.560 --> 28:09.350
Man: Whoo!
Man 2: All right!

28:09.350 --> 28:12.020
(cheers, applause)

